<subSubSection id="BBBBA83D0A597CF73CD78F114670186D" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="943426546BF5362ECE7528EAAF01158A" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB4A07E39CA61554264926A0A44BE81D" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="9D1424BA168A2A33258CECFF6EE96AB0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Lachemilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lachemilla rothmaleriana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rothmaleriana">
<emphasis id="F444088B1B8E1731B7BD3BD85545C2CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Lachemilla rothmaleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a scattered distribution in the northcentral region of the Cordillera Oriental and in the southern part of the Cordillera Central of the Colombian Andes, between 3250 and 3768 m (
<figureCitation id="8A08AE3EE38FF64D9E87055946488941" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Geographic distribution of Lachemilla rothmaleriana (read triangles), L. argentea (black circles), and L. cyanea (cyan rectangle)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.127.36324.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/318148" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.127.36324.figure6">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). This species is mainly found in 
<normalizedToken id="5B20387EA104194165E82D71CDAD1EA4" originalValue="páramos">paramos</normalizedToken>
dominated by bunchgrasses (
<taxonomicName id="F674697430C95898E6ED6DA6116FA30D" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis" order="Graminales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9C124AC9327510D0F46828693369A482" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Agrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0015AD93B012A67FB6A477670B10F1E6" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Calamagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calamagrostis" order="Graminales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="97DFBB3F28ECBADC9EAB3A7C57C6A534" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Calamagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6B07B83F47AD212C88007F4C4C1E3F4D" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chusquea" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C504F5D6C79E9D2ED467401C9D2CFD0E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Chusquea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and lives in sympatry with 
<taxonomicName id="A6518D48FFD2E76C80E72C5C61D16841" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. hipidula" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="hipidula">
<emphasis id="9471AB7556476D2858C7C5BA46A99E73" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. hipidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="001C1074AE12696A07F3254D6E176BF2" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. nivalis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="nivalis">
<emphasis id="ABE74DF1DB8FC4885BC5184FE3391859" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. nivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4F41EDE4E7D29D67EA1B33A5BC34E7AC" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. purdiei" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="purdiei">
<emphasis id="54CC7855FADBDBD436DB2789FABAB41C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. purdiei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Flowering and fruiting collections dated from the months of January, May, September, and December.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EC6CF9710449DDC68830ECF9EB9445B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="27E3DE715FF1B4B789C00C30CED22857" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="71E60296DA1742CAED87419B52D3EFA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
The specific epithet honors Prof. Dr. Werner Rothmaler (1908-1962), a German botanist who studied 
<taxonomicName id="ED8754171E9300DA6BE7FDF8CBD0492D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Lachemilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lachemilla" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0F5BF9D07A82868ABA4612A62DD9A860" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Lachemilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in detail and described over 20 species of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D4E81BC304EF652735F3FB011FF8A0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="4422D16D73836725BBFDB0DDAF767FE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F09759570B4C859344662DE9755868D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="9FA03B11B6A4E075559B49DE9A36A299" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Lachemilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lachemilla rothmaleriana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rothmaleriana">
<emphasis id="5C0B0D63A362FB8AC58C390E5FF2946B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Lachemilla rothmaleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the three localities that are zones impacted by human activities, including conversion to agriculture. Following the 
<bibRefCitation id="66762D4CDDC5A15CA9B997B40C42C4B2" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Plantula" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B4" refString="IUCN, 2017. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
guidelines, based on the reduced geographic distribution and altered land use at the type locality, this species should be categorized as vulnerable (VU).
</paragraph>
