<paragraph id="E4F00DD1197376032303D3B495A72980" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9903AFD502D9CC963904D208E8EBB14" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="D99460D060BB6DDC678AB824458524C1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Lachemilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lachemilla rothmaleriana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rothmaleriana">
<emphasis id="8C7BCB4192BDDF14825937438EFD0F7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Lachemilla rothmaleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="1075E6571AD68DA79540430F0C039F17" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. hispidula" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="hispidula">
<emphasis id="1DAC68F1693AAFF5379FA291C87B6E1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. hispidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6D978A421101E6AD84F7353890A6F44" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. nivalis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="nivalis">
<emphasis id="714078A145CBD56D215C438D74F84AB0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. nivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its habit and erect stems with reduced leaves that fuse with the stipules to form verticillate sheaths, but differs by having trilobate lateral lobes. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="A8825FE42C061719EAD3508B4ADDA70D" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. hispidula" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="hispidula">
<emphasis id="D2696BFCD11603DEECBB6321E23D7B0E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. hispidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an overall hispid pubescence, while 
<taxonomicName id="DB9AD6B5C6DF2FDFCFD81A8C2152F3B3" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. rothmaleriana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="rothmaleriana">
<emphasis id="04B16E8FB33A7F4E9BC6C7DA7A969D06" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. rothmaleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a characteristic sericeous-villous indumentum. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="B0F09465838DD05A0B94DBA19A101433" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. rothmaleriana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="rothmaleriana">
<emphasis id="2438E0063810F9A92DA43834B10F7C8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. rothmaleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a turbinate-campanulate hypanthium with pilose-sericeous pubescence, while 
<taxonomicName id="B43997316F0C3DDB1BB03AD1BCD18F85" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. hispidula" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="hispidula">
<emphasis id="C5F50E6B336CB0FE86D93CCC2DB7BA0D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. hispidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a globose-campanulate hypanthium with pilose-hirsute pubescence. 
<taxonomicName id="BC532E89C5A409AA2F818E1707A2AAE0" authorityName="Rothm" authorityYear="1937" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Lachemilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lachemilla nivalis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nivalis">
<emphasis id="57F4306C255CCDC1998922AE39E0B091" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Lachemilla nivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a hypanthium with similar indumentum but its shape is only slightly campanulate. In the shape of sheath lobes, 
<taxonomicName id="1B7F454AE723BF41204A2CA9AB219FF6" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. rothmaleriana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="rothmaleriana">
<emphasis id="C1979F969E670108CDB73D896C5F9C19" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. rothmaleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName id="0FA4EC048B26D290A97D013406BF1334" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. galioides" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="galioides">
<emphasis id="43D75294E3D162D1A98369F795C9FFCC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. galioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Benth.) Rothm., but the latter has slender stems, broader sheath lobes, and villous-hispid indumentum.
</paragraph>
